There is always some 10x/-1x games to play and always some foundational value plays thereâ€™s also always times to trade and times to invest usually concurrently as well. Most importantly don't use leverage and don't trade ahead of your skis. The worst trade is a forced seller.

Then just know when to rotate the portfolio what to hold ect. Sometimes base moneys are relatively cheap so you want to stack vs riskier assets that have run other times theyâ€™re expensive or itâ€™s very risk on so you want to disproportionately rotate into risk.

Then you have your tee it up and say goodbye bucket where you invest in incredibly risky or scammy things. This is the most fun part and where you maybe identify the meta games early or just -1x all day.

Then you want your meta bucket where you play the hot trade whether it be nfts, defi, alt L1s or just some area youâ€™re really bullish on, curious to hear which one it could be.  This post from @cobie is a great breakdown of this ares. https://t.co/uQma6QdgdD

Then you have buckets in crypto.  Yield farming stables  then value accrual assets btc/USD/eth; you want to stack these core monies. Crypto is benchmarked against 3 value accrual layers.  There may be more or fewer and being right on additional/ fewer is immense alpha. https://t.co/SieVfvhgaM

My best model for crypto is the risk spectrum. You have your buckets for rent, food, leisure, savings/investing. 
In that bucket you x amount in stocks, bonds, cash, crypto, based on risk tolerance/beliefs/level in society/ projection of future incomes/ goals crypto = 5% or 50%.

Human's dying is one of those things in 100-1000 years that we will look back on as a species and think we did we just accept that we had a lifespan.  The only thing preventing immortality is time, and a ton of research/ concerted effort from smarter people than myself.

Any established beliefs or dogmas are more of a harm to progress than radical and subtractive beliefs because progress can only happen through change good or bad. Stagnation will always lead to death. Push the boundaries local maximum are a bigger threat than failure.

The answer to questions of abundance isn't scarcity its always more abundance.  We live in an infinite and constantly growing universe; there is no reason human's shouldn't be immortal interplanetary beings in the next century. Knowledge is infinite and all powerful.

Adidas partnering with @BoredApeYC is just the beginning for the brand. Every brand seeking web3 relevance will make these partnerships and Apes are the clear first choice. TLDR apes are the luxury brand of the future and this brand has a possible 10-12 figure valuation.

Expanding past luxury.  @BoredApeYC is the first native web3 community that is also a luxury brand.  The canonical web2 brand Apple is worth almost $3Tr.  Apes are more than a jpeg; they are legitimacy and a movement at the intersection of culture and technology.

What is the TAM in terms of comparable luxury brands?  Supreme was valued at ~$1Bn in 2017 in their Carlyle transaction while at the high end LVMH and Hermes are valued at ~$400Bn and ~$200Bn respectively.
